Here are 15 factual question-answer pairs based on the provided document page:

1. Q: What is the purpose of the "Vorläufiger Personalausweis" (Provisional ID Card)?
A: The provisional ID card serves as a temporary identification document for individuals who need to apply for a new ID card or passport.

2. Q: Where can I apply for a provisional ID card?
A: You can apply for a provisional ID card at any Hamburg Service office.

3. Q: What is the cost of applying for a provisional ID card?
A: The application fee for a provisional ID card is €10.00, with an additional surcharge of €3.00 if you don't live in Hamburg.

4. Q: Can I apply for a regular ID card at the same time as my provisional ID card?
A: Yes, you can apply for both a provisional and regular ID card simultaneously.

5. Q: How long does it take to receive my provisional ID card?
A: You will receive your provisional ID card immediately after applying.

6. Q: What is the purpose of the biometric data collection process at Hamburg Service offices?
A: The biometric data collection process is used to capture fingerprints, signatures, and photos for the purposes of issuing identification documents.

7. Q: How long are my biometric data stored before they are deleted?
A: Your biometric data will be deleted within 60 minutes if not retrieved, or within 12 hours if not used for another document application.

8. Q: Can I use the self-service terminal to apply for a provisional ID card?
A: No, you cannot use the self-service terminal to apply for a provisional ID card.

9. Q: How much does it cost to use the self-service terminal to capture my biometric data?
A: The fee for using the self-service terminal is €6.00.

10. Q: Can I apply for a provisional ID card without living in Hamburg?
A: Yes, you can apply for a provisional ID card at any Hamburg Service office, regardless of your residence.

11. Q: What are the opening hours for Hamburg Service offices?
A: The opening hours for Hamburg Service offices are Monday to Friday from 7:00 am to 7:00 pm.

12. Q: Can I schedule an appointment online or by phone to visit a Hamburg Service office?
A: Yes, you can schedule an appointment online or by phone through the Hamburg Service website.

13. Q: What is the contact information for Hamburg Service offices?
A: The contact information for Hamburg Service offices includes phone number +49 40 4279-03909 and email address [insert email].

14. Q: Can I access my provisional ID card online?
A: No, you cannot access your provisional ID card online.

15. Q: How long is the validity period of a provisional ID card?
A: The provisional ID card is only valid for a short-term period, usually until your regular ID card or passport application is processed and issued.